cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CE, cs.CR 

The paper deals with game theory and optimization problems in the context of mobile communication services. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves network planning and regulation, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions quality of service (QoS) and suggests the use of optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses competition between mobile network operators, which could place it in cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
